The '''United States Senate election of 1874''' was an election which had the [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic Party]] gain nine seats in the [[United States Senate]].

As this election was prior to ratification of the [[Seventeenth Amendment to the United States Constitution|seventeenth amendment]], Senators were chosen by [[State legislature (United States)|State legislatures]].

==Results==
Senate Party Division, [[44th United States Congress|44th Congress]] (1875â1877)

* Majority Party: Republican (46)
* Minority Party: Democratic (28)
* Other Parties: Independent Republican (1)
* '''Total Seats: 76'''

